title: New Orleans tragedy: Car ploughs into parade crowd
text:
A CAR has ploughed into a crowd watching the Krewe of Endymion parade in New Orleans, critically injuring 12 people. 
The Times-Picayune reports the crash happened on Saturday evening at about 6:45pm, local time. 
New Orleans Police Department spokeswoman Ambria Washington said “initial reports show so far that about a dozen people are in critical condition”. 
That number could increase as the investigation continues, she said. 
More to come.
